<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-703] Change QueryParser to use ConstantScoreRangeQuery in preference to RangeQuery by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-703</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Change to QueryParser to default to using new ConstantScoreRangeQuery in preference to RangeQuery&lt;br/&gt;
for range queries. This implementation is generally preferable because it &lt;br/&gt;
a) Runs faster &lt;br/&gt;
b) Does not have the scarcity of range terms unduly influence score &lt;br/&gt;
c) avoids any &quot;TooManyBooleanClauses&quot; exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if applications really need to use the old-fashioned RangeQuery and the above&lt;br/&gt;
points are not required then the  &quot;useOldRangeQuery&quot; property can be used to revert to old behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch includes extra Junit tests for this flag and all other Junit tests pass&lt;/p&gt;</description>
